@startuml sequence_audit
!theme plain

title Audit Log Creation on Skill Mutation

actor Client
participant "Skill\nController" as Controller
participant "Skill\nService" as Service
participant "Skill\nRepository" as Repo
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Audit\nService" as Audit
participant "Audit\nRepository" as AuditRepo

Client -> Controller: PUT /api/v1/skills/{id}\n{ name: "New Name" }
Controller -> Service: updateSkill(id, payload, userId)

Service -> Repo: findById(id)
Repo -> DB: SELECT * FROM skills\nWHERE id = $1
DB --> Repo: Existing skill (before)
Repo --> Service: before snapshot

Service -> Repo: update(id, payload)
Repo -> DB: UPDATE skills SET ...\nWHERE id = $1
DB --> Repo: Updated skill (after)
Repo --> Service: after snapshot

Service -> Audit: log(action="update",\nresource_type="skill",\nresource_id=id,\nuser_id, before, after)

Audit -> Audit: Enrich with correlation_id\nand timestamp
Audit -> Audit: Scrub sensitive fields\nfrom before/after
Audit -> AuditRepo: insert(auditLogEntry)
AuditRepo -> DB: INSERT INTO audit_logs ...
DB --> AuditRepo: OK

note right of Audit
  Fire-and-forget: if insert fails,
  log ERROR but do not fail the
  primary request.
end note

Service --> Controller: Updated skill
Controller --> Client: 200 OK

@enduml
